INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3000","letter","1778-04-04","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","While General Burgoyne was at General Schuyler's house, in Albany, he wrote as follows to Lord George Germain, October 20th, 1777, concerning the American troops.","ltr_hel3000.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3001","letter","1778-04-08","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","Upon reading the first, I took occasion to intimate to Mr. Duer the distressed situation of his friend General Schuyler, as described by the General himself in a late letter of the 15th of March","ltr_hel3001.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3002","letter","1778-04-27","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","I am directed, by Congress, to request your Excellency will immediately require all officers, civil as well as military, in the army, who are at present delinquent, to comply with the terms of an act of Congress of the 3d of February last","ltr_hel3002.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3003","letter","1778-04-27","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","Your Excellency is too well acquainted with the integrity of your own heart, and too well assured of the good opinion of your countrymen., to admit any anxious impression from the forgeries of an enemy.","ltr_hel3003.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3004","letter","1778-05-03","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","The present will cover an act of that date for ascertaining the rank and pay annexed to Brevet commissions. Whether this is, or is not, intended to have a retrospective effect, I think is not clearly expressed","ltr_hel3004.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3005","letter","1778-05-05","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","Human nature pervades every human breast. A residence at Paris will not exempt men from infirmities of the mind","ltr_hel3005.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3006","letter","1778-06-08","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","My colleague, Mr. Drayton, having shown me, about a fortnight ago, the draft of a report which he had prepared, stating charges against the General Officers who lately abandoned Ticonderoga, and flattering me with assurances that he would soon offer","ltr_hel3006.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3007","letter","1778-06-18","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","Yesterday there was an extraordinary motion on our floor for calling upon members to lay before Congress such letters as they had received from the Commissioners, or other persons, meaning persons in Great Britain, on political subjects.","ltr_hel3007.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3008","letter","1778-07-07","Philadelphia","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","my hearty congratulations with my countrymen on the success of the American arms, under your Excellency's immediate command, in the late battle of Momnouth,","ltr_hel3008.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3009","letter","1778-07-18","Philadelphia","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","Prizes are finding the way into the Delaware. One, laden with rum, limes, &c., intended for the enemy's refreshment, embraced one of our wharves the evening before last, and I learn a rich ship is on her way up.","ltr_hel3009.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3010","letter","1778-08-29","Philadelphia","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","This morning, upon inquiry, I was confirmed in my belief that the former Camp Committee had made no application to Congress for gold or silver, to be deposited in your Excellency's hands for public uses","ltr_hel3010.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3011","letter","1778-10-10","Philadelphia","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","in removing my desks and their contents from one part of the house to a more convenient, I have mislaid among my private papers, and, after as much search at different times, and particularly this morning","ltr_hel3011.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3012","letter","1778-11-20","Philadelphia","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","I believe, and upon good ground, the scheme for an expedition into Canada, in concert with the arms of France, originated in the breast of the Marquis De Lafayette, encouraged, probably, by conferences with Count D Estaing","ltr_hel3012.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_hel3013","letter","1778-04-14","Yorktown","PA","US","Henry","Laurens","","George","Washington","","individual","","Congress, with great concern, perceive that your sensibility is wounded by their resolutions. Placing the firmest confidence in your prudence, abilities, and integrity, they wish to preserve that harmony with you, which is essential to the general we","ltr_hel3013.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
